The paper proposes a method for improving the generalization ability of a primary task using auxiliary tasks without requiring additional data. This is a common problem in machine learning, and the proposed method involves training two neural networks, one for label generation and one for multi-task learning. The paper focuses on image datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the method is also applicable to other types of data, such as text or speech, which could place it in the natural language processing (cs.CL) or neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. The use of meta learning and self-supervised learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Overall, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.NE.
